dback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gaf1665702631801.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gaf1665702631801.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gaf1665702631801.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gaf1665702631801\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n HeaderButton\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__headerbutton_368925\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The HeaderButton is a logical widget for styling a button to look like a column heading.\n </p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__fig_d112574e1_d112575e1_d112576e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Header buttons</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Header buttons above edit boxes in the default entity widget\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/headerbuttons.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure><p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akm1704707836734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akm1704707836734.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\">Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__table_d13376e1_d13377e1_d13378e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Summary</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Logical widget name:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">CommandButton</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Maps to physical widget:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ucmdbutton</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default definition:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">HeaderButton=ucmdbutton(tooltip=on;font=buttonfont;representation=header)</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported triggers and properties:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nnf1665702631473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nnf1665702631473.html\" title=\"The ucmdbutton widget is a button that the user can click to initiate an action. It is a field-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">ucmdbutton</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Use for:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Static or control fields (as defined by the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Static</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Control</span> properties) of type String.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__topic_d79762e1_d79763e1_d79764e1_d79765e1_d79766e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d392957e176\">\n                       \n Grid and MSAA Support\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__table_d13379e1_d13380e1_d13381e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Supported in Grid?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes, but not as column header. Some properties may not be applicable.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clg1695282025414.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clg1695282025414.html\" title=\"The egrid widget displays data in a tabular format, in which the rows are occurrences of an entity and the columns are fields. It is an entity-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">egrid (Grid)</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jaw1718600633504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jaw1718600633504.html\" title=\"The Check Box, Color Box, Combo Box, Command Button, Drop-Down List, Edit Box, Picture, and Spin Button are supported in the Grid widget, but many of their properties are not.\">Widgets and Properties Supported in Grid Widget</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Supports MSAA?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">No.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__topic_d79767e1_d79768e1_d79769e1_d79770e1_d79771e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d392957e245\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__p_d112583e1_d112584e1_d112585e1\">The HeaderButton is typically used as a column heading when styling an entity as a table, but without using the Grid widget. The HeaderButton follows Windows conventions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gaf1665702631801__p_d112586e1_d112587e1_d112588e1\">The text displayed on the button comes from the field value.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxc1665702631725.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Defining Command Buttons</a><p>Command buttons enable the user to perform specific actions. They should only be used in form components, not in reports.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qvt1665702616238.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>KeyPadEnterAccess</a><p>Specifies whether the keypad Enter key is routed through the keyboard translation table for command buttons.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527764\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527764\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "HeaderButton Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 HeaderButton The HeaderButton is a logical widget for styling a button to look like a column heading. Figure 1. Header buttons For more information, see Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity . Table 1. Widget Summary Logical widget name: CommandButton Maps to physical widget: ucmdbutton Default definition: HeaderButton=ucmdbutton(tooltip=on;font=buttonfont;representation=header) Supported triggers and properties: See ucmdbutton Use for: Static or control fields (as defined by the Is Static and Is Control properties) of type String. Grid and MSAA Support Supported in Grid? Yes, but not as column header. Some properties may not be applicable. For more information, see egrid (Grid) and Widgets and Properties Supported in Grid Widget . Supports MSAA? No. Description The HeaderButton is typically used as a column heading when styling an entity as a table, but without using the Grid widget. The HeaderButton follows Windows conventions. The text displayed on the button comes from the field value. Related Links Defining Command Buttons Command buttons enable the user to perform specific actions. They should only be used in form components, not in reports. KeyPadEnterAccess Specifies whether the keypad Enter key is routed through the keyboard translation table for command buttons. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}